Package: SpatialDataR
Title: Native R Interface to the SpatialData Zarr Format for Spatial
    Omics
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R:
    person("CuiweiG", email = "48gaocuiwei@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides native R access to SpatialData Zarr stores
    without Python dependencies. Reads images, labels, points, shapes,
    and annotation tables from SpatialData-formatted Zarr archives
    into Bioconductor-native objects (SpatialExperiment, SpatRaster,
    DelayedArray). Supports lazy out-of-memory access for
    large-scale spatial omics datasets (10x Xenium, Visium,
    MERFISH) and coordinate system transformations. Designed as
    infrastructure that bridges the Python SpatialData ecosystem
    with the R/Bioconductor spatial analysis stack.
License: Artistic-2.0
